,"Description":"I had to get a lot of work done (several crowns, replace old fillings, two new fillings) and Dr. Wang was AMAZING. Everything was as comfortable as these things can be, no mistakes. Her methods are modern, her staff is friendly and skilled.  I'd recommend her to anyone.  Big fan of Dr. Wang!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDSujh9CpYlwkINMLAKns0cvaQBUCbShAnFyi5ih9TXcFlKvUn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been seeing Dr. Wang for the past 4 years, and I honestly can't recommend her enough. She is the most patient, gentle, and thorough dentist I have ever met. She always takes the time to explain everything clearly and makes sure I'm completely comfortable before moving forward with any treatment. Her skill, attention to detail and gentle approach make every visit feel easy and stress-free.\n\nI'm so glad we found her — it's rare to find a provider who genuinely cares this much about her patients. If you're looking for a dentist you can truly trust, Dr. Wang is the one. Highly recommended!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennie Kh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV48OvuQtTuWa1QLb8SqU1el4YBGIsg4JtHU3-m4WXf0iltGlt9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After years of trying to find the right dental office and dentist, I have finally found the one! Bothell Smiles Family Dentistry is located in Downtown Bothell, near the Bothell Library. The office is tucked away on a street off NE 185th Street, just past the Harbor Homes. They have their own private lot, so parking is easy to find.\n\nMaking an appointment was simple and quick, thanks to the helpful staff. My first visit to the office was back in October 2024. I was seen by Dr. Gillian Lim and the dental hygienist, Ben. Ben performed the initial exam and cleaning, and then Dr. Lim came in to greet me and do one final check and cleaning. The entire staff was very warm and welcoming!\n\nMy first impression of the office and staff was so positive that I decided to bring my parents here as well. During my parents' initial visit, I had the pleasure of meeting Dr. Karen Wang, who was also very warm and welcoming to both them and me. She paid a lot of attention to my parents and made sure they were comfortable during their dental workup. Dr. Wang was very helpful in explaining any additional dental work that needed to be done and made sure to answer any questions I had.\n\nMy mom even praised Dr. Wang for focusing entirely on her--the patient--rather than engaging in small talk with staff while working. She had experienced that kind of distracted care with a previous dentist and wasn't a fan of it.\n\nI would highly recommend Bothell Smiles Family Dentistry and their team to all of my family and friends!\n\nTL;DR:\nAfter years of searching, I finally found the perfect dental office--Bothell Smiles Family Dentistry! The staff is warm and welcoming, appointments are easy to book, and both Dr. Lim and Dr. Wang provide exceptional care. The office is conveniently located with private parking. I've even brought my parents here, and we've all had great experiences. Highly recommend to family and friends!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Weissgarber","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8bgOJ4t4g3mfgeIMKj3_30NYwEp2HSmrKdYbF7JH-iclPTk9hYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve had a fantastic experience at Bothell Smiles and couldn’t be happier with the care I’ve received. Dr. Wang recently performed a filling for me, and she was exceptional. She took the time to thoroughly explain the procedure beforehand, ensuring I felt comfortable and informed. After the procedure, she showed me before-and-after images of my teeth, which really helped me appreciate the care and precision of her work.\n\nThe support staff are equally amazing—friendly, professional, and welcoming, making every visit a pleasant one. I highly recommend Bothell Smiles to anyone searching for a new dentist. They truly go above and beyond to provide excellent care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Allyson Bartholomew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgrXHuIuBK2QHvXr2-OMohGNPAmbhSANxevQMhbxRcmPgYTTl7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We Love Dr. Wang. My whole family has been getting great dental care at Bothell Smiles for years.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tara Tsai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnoyH4C4sjo4L8nDnr1DludKqbUiA0x4MAZKwAUhcjNbi4wA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been going here for several years now and really recommend Dr. Wang and her team. She does a wonderful job with my two kids (ages 2 and 4) who have been going to her since they were about 1. Both of them are excited to go to the dentist rather than nervous. For my own dental health, she is very straightforward and honest which is much better than other dentists I've had in the past. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Y Ni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwJFxdg-uW13Rh_3W40KAe5ZBSK9lfCTHbNn60OUdE00KboA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a wonderful experience with Dr. Wang for a recent deep cleaning. What impressed me most was her patience in explaining the procedure and answering all my questions. She did a fantastic job, and I felt very comfortable throughout the entire process. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jon Wai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGHwFdqGBWpQpCIpTwg2QyAJVYiQrgxObKJ_fM3G6-iF9nzA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience! After almost 30 years with the same dentist, the dentist I had been going to since I was a kid retired. This left me in search of a new dentist, so I decided to try out Bothell Smiles Family Dentistry and I couldn't have been more thrilled to find them. I have been to the office for multiple appointments over the last 5 years and they have all been excellent. Every time I've been, I was greeted warmly, seated promptly, and quickly out the door after a thorough cleaning! Dr. Wang is caring, friendly, and clearly very passionate as well as knowledgeable about her craft.\n\nI have been and continue to be extremely satisfied with the quality of care I receive, and I will be going back!!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"46ac21ce-7019-4b00-b537-410e23c9b838","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Canyon+Park+Dental/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x54900fa9b7f716d1:0xf54f88298b552261!8m2!3d47.789957!4d-122.214882!16s%2Fg%2F1td9q6wp!19sChIJ0Rb3t6kPkFQRYSJViymIT_U?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"17676496774465135201","title":"Canyon Park Dental","categories":["Dental clinic","Dentist"],"category":"Dental clinic","address":"22833 Bothell Everett Hwy, Bothell, WA 98021","open_hours":{"Friday":["8 AM–3:30 PM"],"Monday":["8 AM–5 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["8 AM–5 PM"],"Tuesday":["8 AM–5 PM"],"Wednesday":["8 AM–5 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"http://www.canyonparkdental.net/","phone":"(425) 485-6540","plus_code":"QQQP+X2 Bothell, Washington","review_count":70,"review_rating":4.7,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":4,"2":2,"3":0,"4":1,"5":63},"latitude":47.789957,"longtitude":-122.21488199999999,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEAOVe4pFyu8jLM00fMM7Dh2v8_gNt6nHfUzOMiM1h-QhPDcIs1tjK0dXQmugVp3XdKnH2_-wyGMaBnUm3klDgCuC3tWTc-oIELaKMx7KVnPZbOzPt8lFbuPLLzCmIgLvEw0T_l=w504-h240-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x54900fa9b7f716d1:0xf54f88298b552261","place_id":"ChIJ0Rb3t6kPkFQRYSJViymIT_U","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEAOVe4pFyu8jLM00fMM7Dh2v8_gNt6nHfUzOMiM1h-QhPDcIs1tjK0dXQmugVp3XdKnH2_-wyGMaBnUm3klDgCuC3tWTc-oIELaKMx7KVnPZbOzPt8lFbuPLLzCmIgLvEw0T_l=w626-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=jSvDRwpmDmJfNQFAQppnQQ\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=165.65865\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"117275381761984367733","name":"Canyon Park Dental (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117275381761984367733"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Canyon Park","street":"22833 Bothell Everett Hwy","city":"Bothell","postal_code":"98021","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"lisebinkley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9aw6BWnax2cQkznuF2p9r3nfr5_zHmWwQqBozATWXeOZq6A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Have been going to this office with my family for over a decade and can’t recommend enough! Dr Weller is compassionate and a great professional and the staff is polite and helpful. When you have a toothache they care about it and ensure you can be seen as soon as possible. Thank you ❤️","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kristi Kidrick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-gEIWFUa7LxdDFVqmyD_9zCrLi0lAbIcOhV_00iIGXpmwCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to Canyon Park Dental as a new patient. Had not been to the dentist in 5+ years. I was expecting maybe some bad news. The front office is very calming with a giant fish tank to stare into while waiting. I always have anxiety going to the dentist, and the fish are very calming. Jenna took a bunch of x-rays since I was new, and they had no record. She was very personable and professional with a great sense of humor. I am a research fanatic, so I did my do diligence on the staff and office. I chose Dr. Julie Dawson as my dentist. She is also very caring and has a sense of humor but yet professional. I'm so glad I decided to go here. Best 1st appointment experience I have had in a long, long time at a dental clinic.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mona Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFjysigpt_X4Qz75a98EdxUa5Y7qSXZlFSBlgbYkOZXy14uAfNdw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Disappointed with Veneer Service:\n\nI am very disappointed with my recent experience at Canyon Park Dental.  I had veneers placed on my front teeth by Dr. Dawson about a year ago. Unfortunately, one of the veneers came off within just one year.\n\nWhen I returned to have it reattached, I was shocked to find that I was charged for the procedure. Given the cost and expectations of veneers, I believe they should last much longer without issues. Additionally, I feel that charging for the reattachment, especially so soon after the initial placement, is unreasonable and reflects poorly on the practice's customer care policies.\n\nThe lack of durability of the veneer and the additional cost for what should be considered follow-up care have left me extremely dissatisfied. I would not recommend this dental office to others based on my experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heather Hamilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkuoYHhnwojS6MuSy9jURKFOxeu6gxU9rPpI-8lVCpXBeswQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let me just start out by saying that if you are looking at reviews trying to decide if you should go to this dentist vs another - pick Canyon Park!!! Your search should be over!! This is the most incredible dentist I have ever had the fortune of stumbling into and I can’t thank Tracy and Dr. Weller enough for literally reconstructing my face and my self confidence. I’m traveling in Seattle at the moment and unfortunately managed to significantly fracture both of my front teeth and bite through my lip while here, and I had no idea where to go for help. To make matters worse, I graduate and get married in a couple of weeks and I couldn’t imagine anything worse than showing up without most of my two front teeth. The team at Canyon Park were able to fit me in in incredibly short notice and Dr. Weller and Tracy not only fixed my teeth, but made me feel so beautiful by remedying some other insecurities I had about my smile while they were at it!!! They were extremely kind, understanding, and gentle regarding my dental anxiety as well. I can’t stop smiling now, and they managed to turn a fairly traumatic event into the biggest relief. To top it all off, their front desk staff are amazingly kind and were so helpful with all my billing questions and concerns. If you ever find yourself without your two front teeth (or just need a cleaning), don’t hesitate to go meet the wonderful people at Canyon Park!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Inna Polonsky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVTIz6fVsCsppnixfeXrSaq3zOoTI0NVyst9dnw3_HsFKAHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From the first day I set my foot into this office, I have found nothing but professionalism and skilled individuals,  from the receptionist, office staff, dental hygienist and Dr. Kalvish!\nThe dental hygienist, Malacha, was very friendly, professional and her work skills are excellent and thorough.\nDr. Kalvish is just wonderful! Very knowledgeable, gentle and does a great job all around! He takes time to answer questions and I never felt rushed.\nDental assistant, Kirsten,  is very kind, personable, courteous, accommodating  and excellent in assisting doctor.\nI highly recommend this dental office to everyone!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Wendell Mushrush","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIdAIX9uFzJF8RFyIbwz4xHlRmXPGpLekPxjpo1z6U_0iqS6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm 57 years old and have found the best dental clinic ever ! They're very professional and courteous but being personable I would say is why I continue my dental needs there. They've always accommodated me in every way making return visits a breeze. I've done a 180 from hating dental work to enjoying my visits. The work there is above and beyond what I could've hoped for. Thank you Canyon Park Dental for everything you do in making sure you go above and beyond this patient's needs !","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJZ57VYmDqs-7FptigozReHDUAnkOeVKQFLDMo_g3AYh3vT0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"*****BEWARE IF THE TELL YOU THAT YOU NEED A TOOTH PULLED ********\n\nAfter not seeing a dentist for 3o years and still no cavities… gums ok… no major issues.  Started being seen on regular basis after almost a year I got infection under my tooth.  After one week medication AND NOTHING ELSE….I was told it needed to be pulled.  This was in APRIL 2023.  I went out myself bought a mouth wash got another round of meds…(THEY ARE STILL TELLING ME NOTHING ELSE CAN BE DONE BUT PULL IT.\n\nI was mocked by staff, laughed at then talked to owner who proceeded to agree with his staff.\n\nI waited to write this….7 months later not one issue\n\nThey would have pulled for what $100… but a crown is thousands of $$$$… they mocked me and laughed.  Do you want that or to have a tooth pulled for absolutely no reason????\n\nTHINGS THAT MAKE YOU GO HMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMM\n\nI WOULD NEVER SUGGEST ANYONE GO HERE","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jose R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1jVSGXbuLSuxAMhZZW_ItBAItG_6XCcnQQQeNbrhLug4mUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went to canyon park dental for a cleaning. however, before I did anything I asked them to make sure I was covered by my insurance. they assured me aside from my copay, I was totally covered. I was not and I ended up getting sued because of them two years later.\n\nafter a check up they told me I needed a \"deep cleaning\" as opposed to a regular cleaning and I would need to schedule another visit. I went to schedule another appointment and the receptionist insisted that I schedule four separate appointments as opposed to one because the cleaning would take a long time and \"it would be easier on the doctor to not have to sit with one patient the whole day.\" I told her I would rather do it all at once but she reassured me that it would not affect how much I pay and my insurance would cover all four visits the same as if it was just one. reluctantly I said ok and scheduled the four visits.\n\nI payed my copay and to my surprise I was asked to pay a copay after every appointment despite them telling me it would be no different than if I had I just scheduled one appointment. after every appointment I paid in full and I thought that was the end of it. then, weeks later I received a text message from them saying that I still owed them somewhere around $450-$500 because my insurance did not want to cover all four visits. they did however say that it was not right for me to have to pay it and they would fight the insurance and take care of it. after months they told me the got the balance down to around $100.\n\nI paid what I owed after every visit. I asked them multiple times to make sure my insurance would cover it. they assured me I would only have to pay my copays. I payed what I owed and this was their mistake. rather than doing what a respectable business would do and admit their mistake and let the $100 go, they sent me to collection and the collections company sued me costing me more than what I initially owed.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails