 \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=bs7dWYafJ0xYq23sxxrfmw\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=319.68866\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.myidealdental.com/shoreline/book-appointment?utm_source=gbp\u0026utm_medium=organic\u0026utm_campaign=book_appointment","source":"myidealdental.com"},{"link":"https://schedule.jarvisanalytics.com/frame/DECA?location_id=6494\u0026rwg_token=AFd1xnFgPIL1-7TC_64CtLrxMkHGj_vmGCnYz88tWI8Q3JJNYhZHKnbd7Yb1rxnj62COavpVy-YMzeQ8NpXRn0iHIMqNyz9DyRuCF5OiZ_vWYOHZen5QVLk%3D","source":"jarvisanalytics.com"}],"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://www.myidealdental.com/shoreline/services%3Futm_source%3Dgbp%26utm_medium%3Dorganic%26utm_campaign%3Dservices\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwjRya3Fk9CUAxXtEzQIHSVWAFgQqRkIHSgQ\u0026usg=AOvVaw0FFoZDmvko57mCwr3cU7el","source":"myidealdental.com"},"owner":{"id":"104366685387852721335","name":"Ideal Dental Shoreline (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104366685387852721335"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Ballinger","street":"20011 Ballinger Way NE Ste B-100","city":"Shoreline","postal_code":"98155","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Gabriele Peterson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyN-YCzTrySozmYe7uhM1WVMKtkjce7x6bZ_WyNyxlInvDnKeX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I would not recommend this practice to those with dental anxiety. If getting dental work isn't an uncomfortable experience for you, the employees were lovely, their imaging equipment is advanced, and the provider seemed to know what he was doing. I have severe dental anxiety, and normally need to have nitrous even at cleanings. I verbalized this to the scheduler when I made the appointment, and the front desk, the dental assistant, and the doctor at the time of my appointment but ended up having a panic attack after a tool poked me a little too hard in the gums. I was then told by the dentist that I should have told the front desk at check in. Personally I will not be going back as a practice where I have to scream to be heard does not align with my needs as a patient.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Crystal Hawkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJA7ql9nbJ8jpIipPhshLnXvbSD3dhvTLuCbh7M7Rj4uqUygg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I rarely leave reviews but wanted to warn others away from this location in Shoreline.\nMain issues: doctors don’t trust each other and they overcharged and won’t return calls.\n\nOne issue is with the billing… they took a long time while I waited in the chair to confirm my insurance coverage and billed me over $300 (so I assumed it was an accurate estimate). Then my explanation of benefits noted my portion should be $114 and I’ve been unable to get a response for 2 weeks. They make you pay in person so there’s a reasonable expectation they’re accurate or would correct if something changed. Not so.\nAnother issue is the staff: dental assistant had zero “bedside manner” and flat out wouldn’t listen to me. The doctor corrected her actions while working in my mouth and also belittled a new doctor while boasting himself. I resolved to find a new dentist when only a couple days later the new filling fell out and I was forced to return - same terrible experience with the assistant and a new doctor who was also quick to blame and belittle the previous doctor.\nDon’t trust this place for anything! They don’t even trust each other and they can’t get the billing right and then won’t return a call to address the discrepancy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angie M (Angie)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9fNgxdyuQNJN16xtntCAs_o6lmjdxLmajDUFEI6u7M6tmSpAG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I finished orthodontist with great ortho care. Came here and the dr shaved off 3different visits my #7 tooth. The color was wrong first time and not fit so he drilled off the tooth again and put on a veneer that does not fit and the back of tooth hits my bottom tooth when trying to eat. My tooth is now loose, wrong color, food stuck under it and Dr . Said he shave to much of my tooth of to fix. The reception said that a new Dr was taken over care and the dentist said no he was still doing my care. I left my appointment as this Dr said stop talking and wanted to stick a sharp tool in my mouth. Very rude and poor quality service. He ruined my poor tooth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hailey Burnett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMhEZOmZqH5WF8DKuATsz3ytl9fx2q311fhUZa9EVfX2kxag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I highly recommend these folks! Every single staff member was SO kind and they explained everything thoroughly and made sure I understood. After avoiding the dentist for years, they alleviated my concerns so easily. 5/5","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandra Laiblin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4yUCtfohmsyzjWoukyLAbBme4UWyGFowIuhaGezTmyYWMOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"My review comes from declining quality of care moreso than about staff; staff members at this location have always been pleasant when I've gone in. When reflecting on my last couple bi-annual appointments, I have come to the conclusion that the quality of care is not what I want from my dentists office. I feel like I come in for 30-45min and receive the bare minimum. This was especially true of my most recent visit; my teeth were polished first before anything else was done, which I thought was strange as polishing has been a concluding treatment with other past offices I've gone to. And then the dentist came in, blew air around my mouth, scaled my teeth, and was done. I wasn't due for xrays at this visit, but I dont feel like a thorough oral exam was performed, the dentist didn't even take gum measurements which has been done at other offices I have gone to because it helps track any gingival recession. Preventative healthcare is important in order to stay ahead of any potentially expensive or harmful health issues, and I do think I will be looking for a dentist that provides more thorough prophylactic dental care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"BARB ROSENGRANT","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxAz8oF_rvlJpS9WDxpmycvx9RSz6QhODOUURK02cETRbVFx61=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Dentists and staff were great, kind and very gentle while taking care of my teeth.  I have always had bad experiences going to the dentist, but IDEAL made it so easy.  Thank you for making my visits almost stress free.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Margaret Connor (MeiBirdy)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8voeDwuNZ3mZuTmWQoxkSV0RobJ_2DIG_WRq9R3OWx0i9ScB8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I have been going to this dentist office since 2023 and was recently billed 1.3K for services dating all the way back in 2023 despite being told I had no outstanding balances across my last regular cleanings. I had active dental insurance during that time and made several payments directly for deductible and out-of-coverage services (Invisalign). This bill was a surprise for me and now I have to track back EOBs for 3 years of services with a insurance company from a previous employer.\n\nI attended regular cleanings and bought into the unlimited Invisalign deal they had, and I am coming to regret this decision.\n\nI stayed with this office because I liked their front of house and hygienists, but at my last appointment found out that they were all leaving the company. I am not interested in receiving treatment from a whole new team with the possibility of a surprise bill. This is very disappointing because the location was convenient and I still have 3 years of Invisalign adjustments left.\n\nThe bill I received also has some outstanding concerns, such as CC payments made in November of 2023 being applied to services received in January of 2024. I am still waiting for a response regarding this bill. Regardless, receiving a bill for over a grand in charges, with no warning and no explanation, while being insured certainly warrants a one-star rating.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Marsters","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKurMUAr1fhZo0CkGbJdJvz2GN1-c3KDZ6uA_2PL3iTy3FjBA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An excellent experience dealing with Ideal Dental Shoreline. Everyone went out of their way to make sure the entire process went exactly as we had discussed beforehand, the work was excellent and the costs were explained in detail. I have worked with Ideal Dental for over a year now and have had only good results from them.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
