menities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"nathaniel orr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIdBsu5dHC5pkL0wVHC8tpw2D1kw6v1rnJlOh0aPnGf64fkFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I show up not wanting to be there. Ana immediately  helps me shes kind and warm and welcoming.\nSo I get called back by Rebecca and go to the big scary chair in the back that I have been dreading and get situated. She's very kind i tell her im very nervous and i brought some emergency anxiety meds just in case (i didnt need them) and she immediately gets me engrossed in a conversation to keep me distracted and it worked...its like i have known her my entire life and while we are doing the full workup theres no falter in what i was assuming to be a façade. she seems to actually care about her patients....this is crazy this is so different from what i was expecting...so i stayed.....I see Dr. Yashi\nand thats when i knew shes my dentist. She starts with hey....this isnt as bad as it could be....and she breaks down multiple plans with multiple contingencies as we explore more into my mouth health. Not ONCE did anyone make me feel ashamed..not ONCE was she harsh...NOT ONCE DID SHE MAKE ME FEEL LESS THAN FOR MY CIRCUMSTANCES. She put 3 whole plans together let and let ME choose how I would receive care, she gave her professional opinion on what needed to be taken care of first so...gaining my trust i went with her recommendation. We cleaned my teeth up that day and went home less afraid of the dentist. it cost me almost nothing. I went to see Ana and she broke down all billing. Ana scheduled my apt for the following Friday to have....what i dreaded most....a root canal. Ive heard about these....i didn't want any part of it, but Dr. Yashi gave me confidence in her skillset and told me we might not have to move forward with it that it really depended on the state of the tooth when we got down to it. So it was either a root canal or a crown depending.\nFast forward one week to my actual procedure day (today)\nI go in without my partner because...quite frankly i felt at home in this dentist office so i wasn't anywhere near as nervous or anxious. Ana helped me get checked in and Nickole was my dental assistant. I had not met Nickole last time, but sure as sugar she was kind, understanding, and had an amazing table side manner. Just like the previous dental assistant i got engrossed into conversation and my fears melted away.\nOK TIME FOR PROCEEDURE. Dr. Yashi comes in and she gets me nice and numb i feel a prick in my upper mouth area and then...NOTHING no pain no nothing my mouth is completely numb....my brain was trying to get me to feel hurt but Dr. Yashi got that good stuff in there. Now there were a few wince moments but it was perceived pain not actual pain. Any time i winced or showed any discomfort Dr. Yashi and Nickole were there to make sure i wasnt hurt or uncomfortable. I felt so safe....so secure and so cared for....no lie i almost fell asleep in that chair. Fast forward im dozing chilling in my lil throne of dental opulence i realized something....I am going to be able to smile again....without feeling ugly...im going to be able to take pictures with my family again and not have a closed lipped smile...im going to be able to kiss the love of my life full on the lips again and not be self conscious because the teeth rotting in my head give me terrible breath and i  feel my eyes start to water....not from pain...not from fear...but hope... Thanks to Woodinville Modern Dentistry I have hope again.\nNever thought I would say this but I CANT WAIT TO VISIT THEM AGAIN.\nSorry I know that this was long winded but I really need ANY BODY READING THIS that is unsure and needs help with their dentistry to give them a try. They are amazing, they deserve to be successful because they have what so many people lack these days.\nEMPATHY\nKINDLESS\nand most importantly\nCOMPASSION.\n\nTo my dental health team...thank you from the bottom of my heart. I can show the world my new beautiful smile. I can express how I feel without being ashamed and most importantly...I have hope again.\n\nP.S. I forgot her name but there is a dark haired receptionist that also helped while Ana was away and she was just as kind and sweet as everybody else","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2h1DAJiTyZs_wSgTOlPabimUS8uKKQXf0eRkDF6kYOwP8brIHPvGseti7U69kViXAW8tviNGJ7heZxmadNCdqvIPvW7dUHGQGfb4D0ex1JSiNZEl6RHMDdJhgxCsK1WdePK3ar6yhCN661=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-30"},{"Name":"EH G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKsdPTCDVX-aaCfaX1sDJtwRcW66RlaxqszgsYz0GhvKM5wfw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall, the office is great! Anna and Christine at Reception are phenomenal. Dr. Lee and his Perio Assistant are also fantastic. They clearly explained my recommended short-term and long-term treatment plans, as well as the portions of treatments my insurance would cover.\n\nMy only disappointment was with Dr. Kaur, who I saw for my initial visit. She left me waiting in the chair for half of my 1.5-hour appointment while she attended to other patients. I didn’t even receive the cleaning I’d scheduled on my first visit. She also had the receptionist book me for unnecessary services I hadn’t agreed to, which I then had to cancel pending a consult with Dr. Lee. If I hadn’t waited for Dr, Lee’s consult, I would have paid $1,000 out of pocket for treatment that wasn’t necessary.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gelo Time","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDcf_-TzIP8Va3AnjU98SG4P-f3V4qgbCIQArK-PxTqEIn4poR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a first time patient, the staff and atmosphere were so welcoming. I transferred from a different clinic and was concerned about the process of getting my paperwork, xrays, etc in order. However, Dr. Choi and the team made the experience extremely smooth with great knowledge and expertise. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashlee Ashlee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDqssdkpFflKvAHXFF3v4u3Hs3gC8uBo2uamN6KVj3wFJRAdv-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have never in my 26 years of living had a greater dental experience than I did at Woodinville Modern Dentistry. I mean I seriously could not recommend this place enough (and I indeed will recommend this clinic to every single person that I know.)😄\n\nI’m somebody who has TONS of health anxiety and even more when it comes to dentists due to some unfortunate experiences I had at my last dental office. My fiancé recommended I check out this place after his visit and I’m so beyond happy that I did. For starters, Anna at the front desk was absolutely wonderful. She was so welcoming, so kind and helped set me up with a financial plan that made my visit so insanely affordable for the care that I received. My dental assistant Rebecka was an absolute ROCKSTAR! From getting all the basic vitals, to taking X-Rays, down to the saliva test she took her time to explain everything she was doing and was so empathetic and so kind during the whole process. She was quick, super efficient and truly such a professional. My dentist was Dr. Choi and I don’t have enough positive things to say about her! She really listened to all the concerns and worries that I had and didn’t just brush them off like some dentists have to me in the past. You can really tell how passionate she is about her job through the care that you’ll receive if you have her as your dentist. She was incredibly thorough, she even spotted a small cavity that my last dentist missed, she gave me SO much incredibly helpful information and had me leaving so much more confident about my oral health.\n\nI’m really taking my time writing this review because I feel that it’s so important that people understand the quality of every single person working in this clinic. I genuinely have never had a better experience and for the first time in my life I really look forward to getting my next cleaning because I know I’m in good hands here. HUGE thank you to everybody at Woodinville Modern Dentistry, you have no idea how much you’ve shifted my mindset on dental visits and I couldn’t be anymore grateful for you wonderful people!🥰","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Murron Wake","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUO8Sr_JT4sAvT8JI3f1cQ5ReA0Rx-tGe8gl1Dm5T58M-L8Nzok=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I tried this dental office after moving to the area because of its great reviews. My visit began with X-rays and a saliva test. Dr. Baljinder Kaur said my bacteria levels were high and that I had several 5–6 mm gum pockets, diagnosing periodontal disease and recommending deep cleanings, laser therapy, and irrigation.\n\nI was then given a treatment plan totaling about $3,200 (four visits per year at roughly $800 each), which was shocking since my insurance only covers two standard cleanings annually.\n\nI’m almost 30, have never had periodontal disease issues, brush and floss regularly, and have kept up with routine cleanings my whole life. When I asked if I could at least receive a standard cleaning that day while I took time to consider and plan a budget and timeline for my options, Dr. Kaur refused, calling it “patient neglect,” and appeared frustrated when I didn’t immediately agree to the proposed treatment plan.\n\nWhile the rest of the staff and treatment coordinator were kind and patient, the overall experience from the doctor felt manipulative and added an overwhelming amount of pressure for a first visit.\n\nI left without any treatment and sought other opinions. I consulted another dentist right away, and—just out of curiosity—also had my X-rays reviewed using AI, and nothing concerning was found. My previous dentist also confirmed that no extensive treatment is needed.\n\nI was very disappointed with the dentist’s refusal to perform a basic cleaning. The experience felt more focused on pushing expensive treatments than on patient care. The whole experience just felt off and I’m glad I listened to my gut to leave. I would strongly urge others to seek a second opinion before going here!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Greg Kaewpunpong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXKhbXqrGhVWiVdgp1l4_v9UpNIsjSXeiLVC5OZmmf8A9F5_QP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am so happy to have discovered this dental clinic. A special thanks to Christina at the front desk for her warm welcome, her smile really put me at ease. Dr. Kaur provided a very detailed examination before the procedure, and Dr. Reji was incredibly patient throughout the long treatment, answering every question I had. And they all in this clinic are so kind 😃\nIf you are deciding whether to come here, I 100% recommend it.\"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Priscilla Franco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJc6nMjDYtgxoGbI_GU0oasM84dw0LneNTc6GAgp3Uf_TC-LA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my daughter’s first visit to this dental office, and we couldn’t have had a better experience. The staff was incredibly thorough and took the time to explain everything clearly, which made both of us feel comfortable and informed. They were transparent about the process, cost, and any recommendations, with no pressure at all. Everyone we interacted with was professional, kind, friendly, and patient. We truly appreciated the care and attention they gave, especially for a first-time visit. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aryna Andriichenko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsFoQ1wG-qqCoMBoB9kzs030s4Kp1nbonI-k26fecEVuJnAZUC_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been seeing Dr. Choi and DA Shahd regularly for maintenance, and I couldn’t be happier with the care I receive every time. The office is always clean, organized, and welcoming. The entire team is friendly, professional, and makes me feel comfortable from the moment I walk in ❤️👍","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
