are so kind and helpful, thorough in their exam and care, and just so good at what they do!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW90EBTOxLLA29rflaVwJebHfU9240V7_3fJ2UKIwLjIbvZPTo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"***SCAM***I had a terrible experience with Sunrise Dental and feel completely scammed. Before my treatment, I was clearly given a price and agreed to move forward based on that amount. After the service was completed, they kept sending additional bills asking for more money with no clear explanation. In the beginning you get a great quote but afterwards they keep sending you additional bills. STAY AWAY FROM THEM!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lucy Zheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHS0AlF2FnQluYbwMQMpr1VkjjTOwnTWc8WJA6TpbJKluVzx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This is an okay place to go for regular, preventative cleanings. But be careful if you want to do any other services, because they will quote you a lower price and then bill you five times that amount. Then when you call them, they are not understanding of that at all. You can blame insurance all you want, but it is also your responsibility because we are your clients. This happened with a family member.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michelle Beck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLDV-XjgzNyDjdt9eEq7cEhdXIkjtSrR5gFeAjKOAuvbnFR-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The people who work here are so kind and helpful. I have been once for a routine cleaning, which went exactly how routine cleanings usually go. But what made me write this review is that I was having extreme discomfort due to pain that started in the back of my gums and then radiated to the rest of my mouth and throat over a few days. When the pain started, they had a few openings available, but I had meetings at work I couldn’t move, so I had an appointment for the following Monday. By Friday, the pain was pretty intense, but when I called, they were booked up. The woman on the phone was so kind and sympathetic, and let me know she’d call if anything opened up. She said there was an unconfirmed appointment I might be able to fill if it was a no show. Well, I left work early and waited in the parking lot on the off chance they could fit me in. I went in to check and they went above and beyond to quickly squeeze me in and see what was going on. It turned out to be an infection, which they were able to clean and provide antibiotics for. The pain relief was immediate, and I was so happy to be able to eat and talk without pain, and not have to suffer through the weekend. Thanks Sunrise Dental!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tristan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCEbgHBA6erqGABYkZ4ZBsbeNw4FhsBcLMYaYMS9rhDWeMC2nb4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr Kwon was very professional and helpful with explaining the dental jargon the common folk like me don't fully understand. Referred me to a brilliant specialist for my root canals instead of just doing them for a paycheck. Can't remember the name of the hygienist but he was also awesome and very friendly. Hard to find people like this and restored my trust in dental workers. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Edee AhYat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEaDD6BYYxws4e_aqIL6v6hOgLmScHuXsQeUfI7CiBAzIq340K=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Much of the work I've received has resulted in unpolished work that resulted in discomfort for months after procedures. Most recently, the work that I had done was completed with no care and consideration for aesthetics. When I brought this to the attention of staff they denied the issue, and when pressed, did a rush job of making things \"a little bit better\" etc. The dentist had already removed his lab coat and didn't bother putting it back on to \"fix\" the issue. I felt that the work I received was rushed and not completed with care and consideration for the aesthetic appearance of my smile. Further, during my dental work, the dentist and hygienist were discussing another patient's dental work and they used his name (HIPAA violation).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Morrison","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3dNALp6oxVAZshKEhBQKpWgKu0XNgd5RQLb5lWa7td59g1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 star experience with every single team member here. I'm so happy to find such a hard working, caring group, that showed expertise from each member as I had regular cleaning and work done.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Celeste Carvalho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_GL68L-V-yGwU6FgbOYmOIEgTCrC1DIK6My2vbCXnWDaz1PJW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Out of all the dentists I've been too, this one is by far the best. I felt genuinely taken care of and not taken advantage of. For example, I was really nervous about going to a dentist after years and they explained everything they were doing, took great and delicate care, gave me hope, provided real life conversations that didn't feel forced, and ultimately didn't try to force me into other forms of dental care that weren't needed. They were the best, specifically Dr. Marshall was so wonderful. I know I'll be back again!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
