{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Anant Prakash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHW1bfUA4ufK9D8UcDuPRetTkfc8m6agB1JAiKe-hpUgszGKQIZg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My wife visited this dentistry for check-up and wisdom tooth removal. The check-up went fine, the doctors are courteous and good. But they recommended aggressive periodontal treatment and charged 2000+ (estimate was 200) for it. They do not do pre-authorization with insurance (Premera blue cross) so the final bill can be anything. The front staff was rude and never explained the treatment plan or costs. The lack of transparency and sheer rude behavior from front staff was enough for us to look for another dentist. I hope the owners train the front staff better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chuan Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVcy86euk1N6zJ-at4dWZP3etc3Bn0SsN4kuWs_FDK7NwYutVv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Updated review: In retrospect, I think the clinic is not a bad one. Updating my review to 4 stars. Best wishes to your business!\n\nOriginal review: I came to Redmond Signature Dentistry for a routine cleaning and was told in advance—both by the clinic and my Aetna insurance—that preventive X-rays would be fully covered. However, they performed a periapical (diagnostic) X-ray instead of a preventive one, without informing me, and billed it.\n\nAs a result, I was unexpectedly billed out-of-pocket. When I brought this up, the office manager insisted this is their standard practice, and that patients are responsible for charges insurance doesn’t fully pay—even if the procedure wasn’t clearly explained or authorized. They threatened to send the balance to collections.\n\nThis experience reflects a serious lack of transparency and patient-centered care.\n\n------------------------------\n\nResponse: Thank you for your email confirming the charge has been written off.\n\nThat clarification was not at all clear from the earlier text message, which stated:\n\n“Please pay the balance within the next 30 days to avoid collection. We would prefer not to send you to collection.”\n\nI’m glad the issue has now been resolved, but I want to reiterate that I did nothing wrong—I confirmed coverage with both your office and Aetna ahead of time. If your practice follows a standard of care that routinely involves procedures not covered by common dental insurance plans like Aetna, it is your responsibility to inform patients clearly in advance.\n\nAfter reading other Google reviews, it's clear that I’m not the only patient caught off guard by unexpected charges for so-called \"preventive\" X-rays. This is not about the money—it's about transparency and informed consent. I sincerely hope your office improves communication so future patients can make informed decisions without confusion or surprise bills.\n\nHope your clinic all the best in the future as well!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chakradhar S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpcmwR3REUPhcJc2MLrgS074uJ1txKdkTrboOhctSdgLblPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Very disappointing experience with Redmond Signature Dentistry. The office changed my wife’s original appointment due to their own scheduling conflict. Unfortunately, she was unable to attend the newly assigned time because of other commitments, so she requested to reschedule.\n\nDespite the fact that the original change came from their side, they still charged us a $100 cancellation fee. When my wife called politely to ask if the fee could be reconsidered under the circumstances, the staff was rude, dismissive, and told us we could go elsewhere.\n\nThe issue isn’t just the money, it’s the poor attitude and lack of professionalism. Because of how this was handled, we will be taking our business elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Niamh K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlJuB9hUGD3rxxSo8XlPteZrF71wU-_pQuhTYFtEExs0f_iddQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have attended this location for more than five years. We are very happy. The staff is always polite and friendly, and the office welcoming and comfortable. Dr Stonebraker has a very calming nature, which is great for ND kids or nervous adults.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jamie G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHlLuMu4CbV3DUfWq4Tgr0Ww2M_7p_wmxfBuXgLBFxq4YvQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a rough time finding a good dentist in the area after first experiencing my insurance not covering my dentist, and then a couple of different dentists who retired with, not great substitutes, or moved their locations somewhere less convenient  where I didn't want to round-trip it 45 minutes each way to my dentist.\n\nMy husband and I both moved over to Redmond Signature Dentistry, and have had a great experience for being general twice-a-year to the dentist people without any major tooth/dental concerns. I have not felt like Redmond Signature is trying to upsell me on anything (a weird phenomenon that seems to be hitting dentist these days). They're open and honestly about things like, a couple older fillings their keeping an eye on, or with offering fluoride treatment and noting that my insurance doesn't cover it, but how much it would be to do it out-of-pocket if I wanted to.\n\nEverything has seemed honest, above-board, and professional. They're on-time with appointments. And just overall, happy with the service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sally Rodgers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLhHvzaCvEuZhC1Nl1DhFcZTBMch1zGJNcdxC4bLvXAtKwHRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The patient care at Redmond Signature Dentistry  is unlike any I’ve had before. Instead of dreading going to the dentist, I look forward to seeing the wonderful, caring Doctors and staff. They work to make your procedure as comfortable as possible and help you feel like you have control over your oral health.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anil Vattikuti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsl_AAPUY7XQ2_hKPkz3DRfx4cZys2sEesbyTBAZRwWIE6E_o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a fantastic experience with my doctor , hygienist and whole team at this place. Everyone is super friendly and makes you feel comfortable as soon as you walk in. They’re always thorough and take the time to explain what’s going on with my teeth in a way that actually makes sense. It’s great to feel like you’re in good hands and not rushed through. Definitely recommend if you’re looking for a great dentist and a team that truly cares.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jewell Sanders","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwl31nhQXRDhKacrmSarWIo2SVYmxOSy1Co43emWEvja1FuN1c=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I travel around the country a lot for my husbands work, which means I meet a lot of dentists because we’re good about getting our teeth checked every 6 months regardless of where we are. This practice is probably the best one I’ve been too. Beautiful facility, very friendly staff, and most importantly a thorough exam and cleaning. They took their time going over my X-rays with me and cleaning my teeth. I so appreciate this! Some places like to hurry you in and out in 30 minutes or less. Not this place! I left feeling confident my teeth were sparkly clean. I even scheduled my husband an appointment while I was there. And I’ll probably schedule my baby one too! Thank you Dr Jeff and Iris!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
