ns":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Charlyn Gomez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLR9kV3_8wopyNNVTO65dUUsvkSjjCB23Gu6W3wT4H8aK6eig=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Advanced Care is the best dental practice. The staff is friendly and caring; their office is clean and well maintained; we have 3 insurance payers so billing can get challenging but they handle it all, with patience. If a dental emergency arises, there is always a dentist on-call. We get consistent reminders for appointments. They deserve these 5 stars!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Negar Motazedian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVcReuUd-27F7lrlLkXlnZ58FyrX697ePOo2jr7TXQhBbsDw2g5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I would give this place negative stars if that were possible. This is nothing short of a scam.\n\nI was explicitly told that they are contracted with my insurance and that my routine cleaning would be covered 100%. Despite this, my so-called “annual cleaning” ended up costing over $500 even with insurance, which is completely unacceptable.\n\nThey quietly add charges without disclosure—most notably fluoride, which is commonly offered at no cost elsewhere, but here they charge $61 and never mention it in advance.\n\nEven worse, after the fact, they claim that routine cleanings are only covered 80% under their contract, directly contradicting what I was told beforehand.\n\nThis is a complete lack of transparency, misleading communication, and a terrible patient experience. Proceed with extreme caution","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniela Cubreacov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJ4iJNRVFth1ayIb5uReTx7AXJWwKe-kqCQPHfC_gbVo5xcYVYzA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My dental hygienist, Laura, is the best!!! She is so gentle and always takes time to educate me about how I can take care of my teeth better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelley Long","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlc6zr7W1iDUKHV0YKjgXDNTnODUbFMaCJsJOMnbsiNx-gZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Marxen and his team were kind and thorough! Very grateful for his care!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hank","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ4BBEaXbHoF_hsVbbC_IWEvjFrtaioWGHuDOI-vU5XGx7Y1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly professional team supporting the complete dental service. Need a crown within a few hours you'll walking out with it unlike other places I've been.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Corbett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT7Dqq2H1V0dPh0ZAeP35hjnKBLIjX164tN-pheeL2GSffgsns=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Advanced Care Dentistry is a hidden gem in Woodinville featuring the amazing Dr. Marxen.\nHere’s why you will enjoy being his patient \u0026 why it’s the only place you will ever need (from a patient of 17 years):\n\n1. Multiple ares of expertise \u0026 Certifications~\nHe is a Dentist AND Endodontist.\nHis (rare) specialty is Perio-Prosthesdontist for which he is an international Lecturer \u0026 featured guest Speaker.\nI value his expertise in Restorative Dentistry \u0026 his aesthetics in creating realistic teeth that match the patient’s existing teeth’s shape \u0026 color to look both real \u0026 natural.\nYou can go to ONE place \u0026 get ALL of your dental needs taken care of.\n\n2. He’s on the leading edge of research \u0026 treatment for his patients as a UW faculty member, teaching in the School of Dentistry.\n\n3. As a published author in the area of Perio-Prosthodentistry, he is an expert in the field and his patients benefit immensely from his specialized knowledge.\n\n4. His staff of dental assistants \u0026 hygienist all love working with Dr. Marxen at Advanced Care Dentistry, meaning he attracts the best professionals with everyone positive \u0026 happy, making for a wonderful patient experience.\n\n5. Cutting-edge use of technology including 3D cameras \u0026 scanners, 3D printers that quickly \u0026 conveniently make crowns on-site in only minutes, stem-cell spinners for fast \u0026 effective healing and more! Really amazing!!\n\n6. Pain free treatment options like nitrous \u0026 sedation.\n\n7. Outstanding maintenance \u0026 cleaning programs for extended \u0026 long term dental health. A focus on affordable regular prevention is important \u0026 appreciated!\n\n8. Dr. Marxen is an engaging, interesting \u0026 “real” guy who has raised a family in the area, coached local youth sports teams \u0026 enjoys the many activities the Northwest provides. You feel important as a patient as he easily connects personally with everyone.\n\nNeed dental work of ANY kind? Feel good knowing you’ll receive the best, most comprehensive \u0026 professional attention from Dr. Marxen \u0026 the team at Advanced Care Dentistry!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn09B3Uu8lrDlZi7A-iONK7inGvEMxSeq3X-JlPZpvagpKBZ6KOyQkPNOm-JQj0iVQ-_aWX6UpEkEh-65PAdRBuSeth5HgeU4jBpXTXRTRo4gpSKbKBWndHrjNcbDLZP0ufEfYI=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn32Dt1eqDmrGq144qydgnTFYG-bqZ-Xmqz8clxmzdAxRL0FVgRbUqZQsVnJEcz_LNfcjXmTfe03qit1whloS2Us08uTDTmdU1RYchG-LzApQNBS2-0IhgfhmaDeKvE-DRidnxnQFQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1vJMalsdhy4-PYaIEW9CJgPgpDWUkgFkTj0KE9NX7uAystCe