sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=285.6924\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://microsite.adit.com/b4bb16f6-fad8-4bae-ad25-0824bafdcf26","source":"adit.com"}],"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://www.dentistsnohomishwa.com/services/\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwit6bfLk9CUAxU6EjQIHd39JYMQqRkIHSgQ\u0026usg=AOvVaw10LQZqcVJLtbMev0ByVG3i","source":"dentistsnohomishwa.com"},"owner":{"id":"117038453788469820235","name":"Mountain View Family Dentistry of Snohomish (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117038453788469820235"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"17432 WA-9 #202","city":"Snohomish","postal_code":"98296","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Lorry Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2en7p7RIYg-YqN9Slf8Vxl_lo4U27VcM2td7LMxIL0BWd7CmMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was so nervous! I had put off going to the dentist for over 4 years due to fear. I knew something would happen that would require me to have to go. I dreaded when and what it would be. It happened last night. I lost a filling leaving a sensitive major gap. Searched the web and found the reviews here to be good. They got me right in and had grace for me as I navigated my nerves and opted for the nitrous. My doc and her assistant were wonderful . She helped me connect to my breath as if I were dropping into a guided meditation. My mind drifted away. I felt no pain, remained calm and made it through. I remember feeling seperate from my body as if my soul was merely allowing these women to take care of my vessel. Sounds weird but the level of peace I felt knowing I was being cared for by two women felt very nurturing, almost sacred. I felt proud to let them take care of me and will for sure be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Vette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWD3jSKx-nM4OzMgQ_QisHOSKH0c7h3vCaBdpQ8bKvj3I5p19HQ6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We are incredibly grateful to Mountain View Family Dentistry for stepping up when my daughter was in severe tooth pain.\nThe night before our visit, I called the emergency on-call line. Out of multiple offices I contacted throughout Snohomish County, Dr. K was the only doctor who personally returned my call — and he called me back around 10 p.m. He told me to call the office first thing in the morning and that they would work us in. That alone meant so much.\nWhen we arrived, we were worked into an already busy schedule. We did wait about an hour, but we fully understood we were being added in. The team was kind and communicative — they even gave us a Starbucks gift card for the wait, which was such a thoughtful gesture.\nDr. K took her pain seriously. They repeated imaging and found an infection that had been missed elsewhere. They immediately administered a double dose of antibiotics, sent in a prescription, and helped coordinate care with an endodontist who can provide oral sedation since her infection and pain level were so high that traditional numbing wouldn’t have been effective.\nThey genuinely tried to get her out of pain that same day, and when it was clear she needed specialized care, they moved quickly to make that happen.\nAs a parent watching your child suffer, having a provider call you back at 10 p.m. and then follow through the next morning is something you don’t forget. We felt heard, prioritized, and cared for.\nHighly recommend this office for their compassion, urgency, and integrity.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bill Freiberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDGiLdwZCssoLnao-nWcY6YkAKW29kq04tFAvqrKrQAT3xKA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My initial consultation was awesome. Very polite staff. The Dr made sure all of my concerns were addressed. They offered different treatment options and are willing to help me overcome my fears of going to the dentist!!  I can’t wait to get all of my work done so I can be comfortable with my smile again!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julie Ackley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_0Ji3gqlHC-dhnySjpGZEmMDP_rC8i7kiqN_TfaggqQrxOA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I started with this dentist office. It was my first dentist visit in over 20 years. They made me feel comfortable. They were kind and compassionate. I appreciate the work. They did on my teeth and I appreciate how they handled my dental visits. I did have a problem with their billing. They have since cleared things up. They reached out to me when they saw there was a problem and they resolved the issue. I Understand their concern as I was clearly frustrated and I appreciate they’re accepting their portion of the blame, as I have accepted mine. If you’re looking for a dentist office and this is in work for you don’t wait go. I went at 20 years. They do excellent work! Would definitely recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Derek Livezey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkafHqWqaKTIWmjiLuSXgd57eR8Cn_wxRCgxBzOtzid0hWlZSU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was by far, my greatest experience with a dental office!\nClean, professional, friendly, and very helpful with insurance related information/recommendations.\n\nI highly recommend this office. The staff is genuinely sincere and they have top notch equipment and service. They even took me in a day early as I showed up the day before the scheduled appointment by accident. That flexibility is unheard of. 5+ stars ⭐️ looking forward to get my smile back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shane Robertson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJMoLFdiVecWMbWFx6yM5HOUX41BX9irSjewJBwtFUOdnuStVz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I'm one of the many who have issues with going to the dentist. I usually need drugs and my wife there for comfort. After the second visit to Mountain View Dentistry I felt more at ease than I ever previously have at the dentist. They are kind, calm and attentive to the patients needs. I've had an extraction that went very well. My partial had a tooth added and my upper denture has been relined. I've had my remaining teeth thoroughly cleaned and a couple of cavities taken care of. Most all of this done without me being a total phobic nervous wreck.\nI have never recommended a dental office before, but I am now. These guys and gals rock!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Veronika Marchenko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVh3A1VMYuK6w8JQJIn8AEzDGU5cOwd-dyboQDBjJgzcl_d_Bshfw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This office is so great: Doctor K and Doctor Manvi are absolute professionals who know what they’re doing and deliver the best care possible; front desk girls Jen, Jackie, and Kristen are knowledgeable, attentive to details, and open to help out if any questions arise; dental assistants are caring and supportive; dental hygienists Cynthia and Patricia are such professionals and hygiene-oriented guidances. Very recommend. Come and see because you won’t be disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Declon Gannon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL7Z4FWjjXpz-z1Iqxv-4UpnSY8zZ0qQj3hFDa27sUyD9i-lg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Before starting my review I would like to state I don't know the female dentist as she came after most of my work was done, as for that the only one person I would consider good there would be Cynthia.... All the front staff needs to go back to school and learn basic math as they tried charging me numerous times for hours not there, the assistants are all basic, not well trained and need better help. I went in there letting them know of my needle phobia and how I really dislike dentists, however my last time there I was not given any numbing agent and he straight jabbed the needle in me while holding me down with his other arm..... The crowns I had him do he did completely wrong and were lower then they were suppose to be so my bite was way off. I initially went to him because he kept posting on social media of deals he was offering on crowns, bridges, etc. yet gave me no deal what so ever. He charged the heck out of me and my insurance and I'm having more painful dental issues than ever before. So that being said I would not recommend him to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
